All three failures have the same cause:

```text
savedUser is null
```

In `createUser(...)` you do:

```java
UserEntity savedUser = userRepository.save(user);
```

Mockito returns `null` by default because `userRepository.save(...)` is not stubbed in these tests.

Add this in `@BeforeEach`:

```java
@BeforeEach
void setUp() {
    service = createService(false);

    when(userRepository.save(any(UserEntity.class)))
            .thenAnswer(invocation -> invocation.getArgument(0));
}
```

Make sure these imports exist:

```java
import static org.mockito.ArgumentMatchers.any;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.when;
```

Then your individual tests can remain mostly unchanged.

For the Ping-enabled success test:

```java
@Test
void shouldCreateUserAndSynchronizeWithPingWhenEnabled() {
    service = createService(true);

    UserEntity user = createUserEntity();

    UserEntity result = service.createUser(user);

    assertSame(user, result);
    assertEquals("SUCCESS", result.getPingSyncStatus());
    assertNotNull(result.getPingLastSyncedAt());
    assertNull(result.getPingLastError());

    verify(pingUserClient).createUser(user);
    verify(userRepository, times(2)).save(user);
}
```

For Ping disabled:

```java
@Test
void shouldCreateUserWithoutCallingPingWhenIntegrationIsDisabled() {
    service = createService(false);

    UserEntity user = createUserEntity();

    UserEntity result = service.createUser(user);

    assertSame(user, result);

    verify(userRepository).save(user);
    verifyNoInteractions(pingUserClient);
}
```

For Ping failure:

```java
@Test
void shouldMarkUserAsFailedWhenPingCreationFails() {
    service = createService(true);

    UserEntity user = createUserEntity();

    RuntimeException pingException =
            new RuntimeException("Ping unavailable");

    doThrow(pingException)
            .when(pingUserClient)
            .createUser(user);

    RuntimeException result = assertThrows(
            RuntimeException.class,
            () -> service.createUser(user)
    );

    assertSame(pingException, result);
    assertEquals("FAILED", user.getPingSyncStatus());
    assertEquals(
            "Ping unavailable",
            user.getPingLastError()
    );

    verify(userRepository, times(2)).save(user);
}
```

The important fix is this stub:

```java
when(userRepository.save(any(UserEntity.class)))
        .thenAnswer(invocation -> invocation.getArgument(0));
```

It simulates JPA returning the saved entity instead of Mockito’s default `null`.
